The paper discusses a machine learning problem related to recommendation systems and clustering, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of neural networks and gradient descent methods indicates that it could be in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on non-linear activation functions suggests that it could also be in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The application of the technique to recommendation systems and the mention of user/item features suggests that it could be in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the mention of semi-supervised clustering suggests that it could be in the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
